Parliament, Tuesday, 22 October 2019 – The Select Committee on Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs (CoGTA) and the Select Committee on Security and Justice will tomorrow embark on the second day of their week-long oversight in the Limpopo province.
	
	The Select Committee on CoGTA will tomorrow visit the Musina Local Municipality. The purpose of the oversight visit is to interact with internal and external stakeholders of the municipality as a means of monitoring the progress of the 2017/18 municipal audit outcomes and the audit outcome action plans developed by the district and local municipalities.
	
	Meanwhile, the Select Committee on Security and Justice, which has the responsibility of ensuring accountability for the implementation of security and justice-related strategies, will visit the Beitbridge Border Crossing. The purpose is to assess the responsibilities of the South African National Defence Force (SANDF), the South African Police Service (SAPS) and the Department of Home Affairs in managing the border crossing and the systematic challenges faced by the various departments.
	
	The programme is as follows: ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON COGTA AND THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON SECURITY AND JUSTICE, MR CHINA DODOVU AND MS SHAHIDABIBI SHAIKH.
	
